{"name": "locket", "metadata": {"name": "locket", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: Unix", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "http://github.com/mwilliamson/locket.py", "license": "BSD-2-Clause", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "File-based locks for Python on Linux and Windows", "upload_time": 1650492282}, "documentation": ["# locket.py: File-based locks for Python on Linux and Windows\n\nLocket implements a file-based lock that can be used by multiple processes provided they use the same path.\n\n```python\nimport locket\n\n# Wait for lock\nwith locket.lock_file(\"path/to/lock/file\"):\n    perform_action()\n\n# Raise LockError if lock cannot be acquired immediately\nwith locket.lock_file(\"path/to/lock/file\", timeout=0):\n    perform_action()\n\n# Raise LockError if lock cannot be acquired after thirty seconds\nwith locket.lock_file(\"path/to/lock/file\", timeout=30):\n    perform_action()\n\n# Without context managers:\nlock = locket.lock_file(\"path/to/lock/file\")\ntry:\n    lock.acquire()\n    perform_action()\nfinally:\n    lock.release()\n```\n\nLocks largely behave as (non-reentrant) `Lock` instances from the `threading`\nmodule in the standard library. Specifically, their behaviour is:\n\n- Locks are uniquely identified by the file being locked,\n  both in the same process and across different processes.\n- Locks are either in a locked or unlocked state.\n- When the lock is unlocked, calling `acquire()` returns immediately and changes\n  the lock state to locked.\n- When the lock is locked, calling `acquire()` will block until the lock state\n  changes to unlocked, or until the timeout expires.\n- If a process holds a lock, any thread in that process can call `release()` to\n  change the state to unlocked.\n- Calling `release()` on an unlocked lock raises `LockError`.\n- Behaviour of locks after `fork` is undefined.\n\n## Installation\n\n```sh\npip install locket\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "locket", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "locket._lock_file_non_blocking", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._unlock_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._lock_file_blocking", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._lock_file_non_blocking", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._unlock_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket.lock_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._create_lock_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._acquire_non_blocking", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "acquire", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "retry_period", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "locket._kernel32", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._WinAPI_LockFile", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._WinAPI_LockFile.restype", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._WinAPI_LockFile.argtypes", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._WinAPI_UnlockFile", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._WinAPI_UnlockFile.restype", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._WinAPI_UnlockFile.argtypes", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._lock_file_blocking_available", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._lock_file_blocking_available", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._locks_lock", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._locks", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "locket.LockError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._LockSet", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "locket._LockSet.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "locks", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._LockSet.acquire", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "retry_period", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._LockSet.release", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._ThreadLock", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "locket._ThreadLock.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._ThreadLock.acquire", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "retry_period", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._ThreadLock.release", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._LockFile", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "locket._LockFile.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._LockFile.acquire", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "retry_period", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._LockFile.release", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._Locker", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "locket._Locker.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lock", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "retry_period", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket._Locker.acquire", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "locket.